The paper discusses channel hardening in a large-scale antenna system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of the Reconfigurable Radio Network Platform suggests a focus on system design and control (cs.SY). The analysis of the channel power and delay spread could also be relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.MA) for signal processing and feature extraction.
